\section{Basic use}

Though \pkg{contextual} really comes into its own when you start building your own bandit and policy classes, you can also use one of the package's build-in policies, and run them on one of \pkg{contextual}'s synthetic or offline bandits (see Table \ref{table:overview_policies} for an overview of available policies).

